<br>
To Blackburrow:<br>
If you gate into North Karana, head to the ocean, turn RIGHT (ocean on your left) Put Auto run on and have three cigarettes.  You will have zoned into Western Karana.  When you get to the fishing camp. STOP   Find the woman in armor at the shore, check your friend list for any shamans (approaching level 29 and above).  Ask them if they need their befriend, charm, companion, etc pet spells.  Buffed Charisma, the lowest spell retails at 6 Plat.<br>
Done Shopping?  Go halfway into fishing village, put your back to the ocean, and head that way until you hit a trail.  At the trail, turn LEFT.<br>
Zone into QH and at end of pass, turn RIGHT.  Look for dogheaded entrance.<br>
DREADFUL SKELLIES do hang around here, and can really ruin a lowbies day.<br>
<br>
For those of you going INTO Blackburrow, do this:  Set up camp to the LEFT (as you face it) tunnel to Everfrost. In the corner, near the flats.  STAY OUT OF THE TUNNELS, en masse, as people will not be able to get by you.  If you want to have some fun, camp in one of the first two rooms at everfrost tunnels.  A low Gnoll spawns in each.  Won't it be surprised??<br>
<br>
Bring two fishing rods and 40 bait, you can fish on the 2nd level.  Another good place to set camp is go down to second level and at the base, take a seat on the slant.  ALL trains run by this spot.  (I can't remember, but second level might acutally be 3rd level and you have to go through the third to get to second)<br>
<br>
How is your tailoring skill?  Need to trivial to the lowest at zero cost?  Offer a SOW or other buff for every five gnoll pelts (the stackable ones)  Then take four pelts into large sewing kit and combine, to make a patch of gnoll fur.  Take four patches of gnoll fur, and hit combine to make a gnoll fur quarter.  Take four quarters, make a wish, hit combine,and if successful, you just made a gnoll fur cloak (magic)<br>
<br>
Want to make the newbie's day?  Give him/her some no weight spirit pouches.  TONS of RUSTY weapons drop here, and it is easy to get encumbered.  <br>
<br>
Are you level 20++ and bored?  Come with backpacks of torches and outfit all the gnolls with torches.  Makes it look like a rock concert.<br>
<br>
Top level:  Don't get too carried away or you will fall into the pit, and it is a long way down.  <br>
2nd/3rd level.  You can work your swimming skills here too.<br>
<br>
RABID Grizzly.  No, not a big eared bear, I said RABID.  Keep a cure disease memmed when it pops.<br>
<br>
Teach any level 6-9's to NOT hang near the QH zone, that is where they will surely die, as that is train cental.  If they must hang somewhere to med, do it in tunnel to Everfrost.<br>
<br>
I am betting a monk can practice safefall here too.<br>
<br>
GETTING THERE EARLY:<br>
Any necros going to this camp?  Leave early and get into Everfrost.  Decaying skellies are plentiful.<br>
Sub 20 Rogue?  Go hunt Mammoth Calves and get a Barb friend to give the hides four at a time to the black rogue on the 2nd floor of the bank.  If you get there REAL early, you can get a full set of black wolf rogue only armor this way.<br>
